<subSubSection id="CBC06566FFB7FF96645CFA71FB90FA46" pageId="7" pageNumber="224" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="836536EDFFB7FF96645CFA71FB90FA46" blockId="7.[113,1089,1454,1573]" pageId="7" pageNumber="224">
<emphasis id="B1AEEAFFFFB7FF96645CFA71FF37FA66" bold="true" box="[113,230,1454,1477]" pageId="7" pageNumber="224">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species differs from 
<taxonomicName id="44DA4D6EFFB7FF9665DCFA71FD51FA66" authorityName="Koch" authorityYear="1940" baseAuthorityName="Koch" baseAuthorityYear="1940" box="[497,640,1454,1477]" class="Insecta" family="Tenebrionidae" genus="Tagenostola" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="224" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albovillosa">
<emphasis id="B1AEEAFFFFB7FF9665DCFA71FD51FA66" box="[497,640,1454,1477]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="224">T. albovillosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in shorter legs, anterior tibiae length/width ratio 5.50. Head ratio of width across eyes/cervix 1.79. Elytra narrowed to apex in gentle arch.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
